{"lemma":"لَوْزٌ","slug":"لَوْزٌ","root":"ل.#.ز","root_slug":"ل-_-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-_-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38130"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%B2%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"almond","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"almond tree","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tonsil","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"amygdala","tags":["collective","singulative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic לוּזָא or Classical Syriac ܠܽܘܙܳܐ (lūzā)."},"ipa":["/lawz/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38130","headword_ar":"لَوْزٌ","root":"lwz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"almond;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"almonds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of a certain tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant in the countries of the Arabs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said by some to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mizoj","text_ar":"مِزْج"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that whereof the edible part is not attained save by breaking;"},{"kind":"text","text":"by others said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bruised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brayed,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mizoj","text_ar":"مِزْج"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qumoruwSN","text_ar":"قُمْرُوصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of two kinds, sweet"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bitter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sweet is of moderate temperature, beneficial to the chest and the lungs and the bladder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of its soft nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the eating thereof, shelled, with sugar, augments the marrow and brain, and fattens: the bitter is hot in the third degree, opens stoppages of the nose, clears away"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the spots in the skin called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nama$","text_ar":"نَمَش"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and stills pain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K [but omitted in the CK] and TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its oil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is drunk, and when dropped into the ear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it relaxes the bowels, and causes sleep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the soles of the feet are anointed with it, and when it is introduced into the nose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it is diuretic:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) it is an Arabic word: (Msb, TA:) a coll. gen. n.: (TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.)       -A2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~awozataAni","text_ar":"اللَّوْزَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The amygdalæ of the fauces;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tonsils;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two pieces of flesh in the two sides of the fauces."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two sockets of the hips, where the heads of the thigh-bones are inserted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TS, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}